article.headline: DePaul 61, Dayton 54
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Sammy Mejia scored 23 points and Draelon Burns added 10 to lead DePaul to a 61-54 win over Dayton on Saturday night. Mejia converted a layup with 16:46 left to start a 12-3 run that erased the Flyers' 34-32 lead. Wilson Chandler grabbed 16 rebounds for DePaul (4-3), which shot 44 percent from the field and held Dayton to 35 percent shooting. Monty Scott had 11 points and Norman Plummer finished with 10 for Dayton (6-3), which led 28-27 at halftime. The loss snapped a four-game winning streak for the Flyers, who shot 3-of-17 from 3-point range. It was also Dayton's first loss at home this season. The Blue Demons outrebounded Dayton 37-34 and limited the Flyers to just 28 percent shooting in the second half.
